"{\"uid\": \"theglobeandmail.com-sports-article-gilles-and-poirier-treat-post-olympic-bronze-world-championship\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Piper Gilles and Paul Poirier of Team Canada celebrate their bronze medal in the figure skating ice dance competition during the Milan Cortina Winter Olympics in Milan, Italy last month.Nathan Denette/The Canadian Press  Piper Gilles and Paul Poirier will not call it a last dance.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Piper Gilles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\"}, {\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 29, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}, {\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 44, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.999953383257637, \"rank\": 2.6792064017620385e-05, \"text\": \"Team Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.8153954872814404, \"rank\": 0.2263987421954181, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 135, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4770570429352806e-15, \"text\": \"Cortina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\"}, {\"begin\": 162, \"end\": 167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.8153954872814404, \"rank\": 0.2263987421954181, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 201, \"end\": 219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Canadian Press\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 205, \"end\": 219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Press\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 221, \"end\": 233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Piper Gilles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\"}, {\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But after 15 years and an Olympic medal, next week's world figure skating championships look a lot like a victory lap.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Canadian ice dancers will arrive in Prague after winning bronze with a euphoric free skate at last month's Milan Cortina Winter Games, the culmination of a career built slowly - and on their own terms.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 406, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999607081538328, \"rank\": 3.9292404536950836e-05, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 442, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"score\": 0.9981415865995672, \"rank\": 0.001861847371944663, \"text\": \"Prague\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\"}, {\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.8153954872814404, \"rank\": 0.2263987421954181, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 519, \"end\": 526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4770570429352806e-15, \"text\": \"Cortina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\"}, {\"begin\": 527, \"end\": 539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999900946932, \"rank\": 9.905280767608244e-09, \"text\": \"Winter Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_Winter_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We really want to treat this event as a celebration of our skating,\\\" Poirier said.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics was really the big goal for the season, and we have accomplished that.\\\"\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While some teams - including defending champions Madison Chock and Evan Bates of the U.S. - will skip the post-Milan worlds, Gilles and Poirier chose to give fans, old and new, one more chance to see this season's programs.\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madison Chock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\"}, {\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evan Bates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\"}, {\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Poirier said he's excited to skate with \\\"less pressure\\\" in the Czech capital.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1005, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}, {\"begin\": 1068, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9997438812009953, \"rank\": 0.00012307407907057957, \"text\": \"Czech\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gilles, meanwhile, sees the event as an opportunity to take the ice with \\\"more joy\\\" after a stressful lead-up to the Games, including questionable judging that put their chances of a first Olympic podium in doubt.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winter Olympics 2026: Canadians Piper Gilles and Paul Poirier win ice dance bronze with skate of their lives  An outpouring of emotion - tears, laughs and leaps of joy on the podium - followed their poignantStarry, Starry Nightfree dance in Italy, as Gilles and Poirier finally secured a medal in their third and final appearance together on the sport's brightest stage.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Piper Gilles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Gilles\"}, {\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}, {\"begin\": 1560, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think we intended to be that content after a program,\\\" Gilles said during a conference call Wednesday.\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have always been like, 'OK, we won this event, or we have medalled at this event, now we have something else to look forward to.'\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I think, we just allowed ourselves to be so present in that moment.\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 1988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We were not ready to leave that moment ... even when we got to the podium, we were like, 'We could stay on this podium forever.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gilles and Poirier are already four-time world medalists, having won silver in each of the past two seasons.\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2133, \"end\": 2140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gilles and Poirier react after their free dance during the Milan Cortina Winter Olympics last month.Nathan Denette/The Canadian Press  Both 34, the longtime partners are expected to retire from competition following Prague, though Gilles would not completely shut the door.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}, {\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 0.8153954872814404, \"rank\": 0.2263987421954181, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 2297, \"end\": 2304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4770570429352806e-15, \"text\": \"Cortina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\"}, {\"begin\": 2448, \"end\": 2454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"score\": 0.9981415865995672, \"rank\": 0.001861847371944663, \"text\": \"Prague\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We always lead with our hearts and lead with what our bodies want to do,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We want to just really be present at the world championships and not really have an ending kind of lingering over [us] and, I do not know, having this mindset of 'this could be the end.'\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are just going to leave it open-ended.\\\"\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That did not, however, stop them from reflecting on the mark they have left on the sport, with Poirier highlighting their commitment to a creative, authentic and, at times, quirky style.\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2921, \"end\": 2928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The thing that I am most proud of is our legacy of work, our body of work.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All that we have produced and contributed to the sport and the way that we have always brought ourselves and our vision to what we do,\\\" Poirier said.\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3226, \"end\": 3233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3670485216273487e-43, \"text\": \"Poirier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Poirier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's going to be our legacy more than anything.\", \"from\": 3240, \"to\": 3290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic medal speaks to the amount of work that we have put in and the skill that we have, but I think what makes us Piper and Paul is the creativity that we brought to the sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gilles said that despite their long grind to the Olympic podium, she would not change a thing, comparing their journey to an old fable.\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are likeThe Tortoise and the Hare.\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3632, \"end\": 3640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tortoise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.777371091124477e-21, \"text\": \"Tortoise\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tortoise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tortoise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We get there in the end, and we end up winning on our own time,\\\" she explained.\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I kind of like it the way that we have done it, because if you are successful in the middle of your career and then you are trying to chase that the rest of it, that's really hard.\\\"\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Life since the Games has included time with loved ones - especially after \\\"cocooning\\\" to conserve energy ahead of the Olympics - and a quick return to training just two days after arriving back in Toronto.\", \"from\": 3919, \"to\": 4124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4116, \"end\": 4123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"score\": 0.999987903889122, \"rank\": 1.1993420125360987e-05, \"text\": \"Toronto\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have also had their share of paperwork ahead of an eight-week road trip, including travel visas and taxes.\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rhythm dance is scheduled for March 27 in Prague, followed by the free dance on March 28.\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4285, \"end\": 4291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"score\": 0.9981415865995672, \"rank\": 0.001861847371944663, \"text\": \"Prague\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then comes the show tours withStars On Icethrough the Victoria Day long weekend in May.\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As for what's after that, stay tuned.\", \"from\": 4422, \"to\": 4459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Paul and I will always be involved in skating,\\\" Gilles said.\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So whether this is our last [competition] or we are just doing shows, we just kind of want to still be celebrating what we have accomplished over the last 15 years of our career.\\\"\", \"from\": 4523, \"to\": 4703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Report an editorial error  Report a technical issue  \\u00a9 Copyright2026The Globe and Mail Inc. All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4705, \"to\": 4817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andrew Saunders, President and CEO\", \"from\": 4819, \"to\": 4853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4819, \"end\": 4834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Saunders\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Saunders\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Saunders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Saunders\"}]}]}"